side of the front face is heavily worn.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone.limestone\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html\" cert=\"low\">limestone\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.altar\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/29.html\">altar\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\u003C!--Default values and requires editing-->\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\"/>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\"/>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\"/>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.damaged\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>The text is in small letters across the lower part of the panel on the front face.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.incomplete\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Small neat letters of square form. From the photograph, it appears the sigma may be fairly open, the alpha with straight bar, and the rho possibly with a tail.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n    